This paper discusses the use of deep neural networks and machine learning techniques in drug discovery, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence and machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on one-shot learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and falls under the category of computer vision. The use of graph convolutional neural networks also suggests a focus on computer vision and image analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
